WEBVTT

00:01.833 --> 00:04.000
[serene tone]

00:06.375 --> 00:10.250
- So, Chantal,
I did something for you.

00:10.333 --> 00:14.416
I filed something called
an ineptitude appeal.

00:14.500 --> 00:17.750
Now, this is a leftover
New York state loophole

00:17.833 --> 00:19.041
from the Prohibition era

00:19.125 --> 00:20.833
when people used to be paid

00:20.916 --> 00:23.416
to carry boxes of alcohol

00:23.500 --> 00:24.916
to illegal establishments

00:25.000 --> 00:28.000
without actually knowing
what was in the boxes.

00:28.083 --> 00:29.375
Now, technically speaking,

00:29.458 --> 00:33.166
under this vague
and arcane criminal statute,

00:33.250 --> 00:37.708
you could be considered
a "boxhead."

00:39.958 --> 00:44.625
- For the record,
I never carried anything.

00:44.708 --> 00:47.958
- Uh-huh.
Yeah, I-I-I understand that.

00:48.041 --> 00:50.500
I--what I'm telling you is,

00:50.583 --> 00:53.250
I can get you out of prison.

00:54.041 --> 00:56.291
- Oh.
Whoa.

00:56.375 --> 00:58.333
Okay, just--hold on, Leonard.

00:58.416 --> 01:00.916
Things are moving really fast.

01:01.708 --> 01:03.541
- Do you not want
to leave prison?

01:03.625 --> 01:06.708
- Well, I mean,
I just got used to it, and,

01:06.791 --> 01:09.625
like, the food is, like,
legit yummy,

01:09.708 --> 01:12.291
and, like, the girls here
all think it's really cool

01:12.375 --> 01:14.208
that I did those crimes.

01:14.916 --> 01:16.750
- Okay, you're really
breaking me here.

01:16.833 --> 01:18.625
I j--you know what?
Just--

01:18.708 --> 01:21.458
all you have to do is--here.

01:21.541 --> 01:23.625
Sign this.

01:23.708 --> 01:26.083
- Okay, well, could you,
like, at least give me

01:26.166 --> 01:28.250
five minutes to ask where they
got their mattresses from?

01:28.333 --> 01:30.416
- Just sign the paper,
Chantal, okay?

01:30.500 --> 01:32.375
- [sighs]

01:35.208 --> 01:36.458
I mean...

01:36.541 --> 01:38.166
[sighs]
I don't know, Leonard.

01:38.250 --> 01:40.500
Like, I signed my way
into this mess.

01:40.583 --> 01:43.083
I just--I really think that
I'm gonna need to get a lawyer

01:43.166 --> 01:45.916
to look over this
before I sign it.

01:47.333 --> 01:50.000
- I am your lawyer, you idiot!

01:50.083 --> 01:52.333
You know what?
Just sign the paper.

01:52.416 --> 01:53.750
Sign the fucking paper!

01:53.833 --> 01:55.708
God damn it,
for the love of God,

01:55.791 --> 01:57.625
sign the paper!

01:57.708 --> 01:58.875
- Okay.

02:01.750 --> 02:04.166
I better not go to jail
for this.

02:04.250 --> 02:06.000
- [exhales]

02:06.083 --> 02:09.125
<i>["Obedear"</i>
<i>by Purity Ring playing]</i>

02:09.208 --> 02:14.541
<i>- ♪ Oh, but dear,</i>
<i>the sky is low, watch ♪</i>

02:14.625 --> 02:17.000
<i>♪ Fluent sea men rig... ♪</i>

02:17.083 --> 02:19.416
- It's just so small.

02:19.500 --> 02:22.375
Like, I don't even understand
how we all fit in here.

02:22.458 --> 02:24.916
Like, is this, like,
an optical illusion?

02:25.000 --> 02:27.958
Is there even
enough oxygen to breathe?

02:28.041 --> 02:30.791
- Yeah, I know,
it's a big change, honey.

02:30.875 --> 02:33.791
- Yeah, more like
a small change, Mom.

02:33.875 --> 02:36.291
- Well, we just have
to make do, right?

02:36.375 --> 02:38.000
Robert!
- Huh?

02:38.083 --> 02:39.208
What?

02:39.291 --> 02:41.875
- Okay,
what is wrong with Dad?

02:41.958 --> 02:43.208
- The doctors don't know.

02:43.291 --> 02:44.791
They just speculate

02:44.875 --> 02:47.833
that it's some kind
of situational dementia

02:47.916 --> 02:50.666
brought about
by disturbing circumstances.

02:50.750 --> 02:52.083
- What?
Why?

02:52.166 --> 02:54.208
- Chantal, get a clue!

02:54.291 --> 02:56.083
This is all because of you!

02:56.166 --> 02:58.083
- What...
- Let's not shout,

02:58.166 --> 03:01.583
because we actually do not know
what these walls can handle.

03:01.666 --> 03:02.625
- No, no, Mom.

03:02.708 --> 03:04.791
She needs to understand.

03:04.875 --> 03:06.416
Your legal fees

03:06.500 --> 03:08.583
tapped us out completely,

03:08.666 --> 03:10.875
and now we are poor,

03:10.958 --> 03:14.166
and we all mysteriously
lost our jobs for downsizing,

03:14.250 --> 03:16.458
but it is obvious
that the real reason

03:16.541 --> 03:18.625
is because we have
a family member

03:18.708 --> 03:21.250
that was stupid enough
to associate

03:21.333 --> 03:24.833
with that bad, old man!

03:24.916 --> 03:27.375
We can't get hired anywhere.

03:27.458 --> 03:30.666
They practically chased us
out of Chappaqua.

03:30.750 --> 03:33.125
And you did that to us,
Chantal.

03:33.208 --> 03:34.583
You did that!

03:34.666 --> 03:37.166
- Okay, Catherine,
when you raise your voice,

03:37.250 --> 03:38.958
it is traumatizing.

03:39.041 --> 03:40.166
- Oh.

03:40.250 --> 03:42.958
- You know,
and on top of everything else,

03:43.041 --> 03:45.791
Ted is selling drugs.

03:45.875 --> 03:48.083
- I'm not selling them, Linda.

03:48.166 --> 03:51.458
I'm microdosing,
and it's a legitimate practice.

03:51.541 --> 03:55.125
One tab is 1/12
of a hit of LSD

03:55.208 --> 03:56.416
and can provide me
with a wealth

03:56.500 --> 03:58.416
of incredible innovations.

03:58.500 --> 03:59.625
Believe me when I tell you

03:59.708 --> 04:00.916
I will invent something

04:01.000 --> 04:03.333
that will save our family.

04:03.416 --> 04:05.541
- Ted, my family

04:05.625 --> 04:07.166
is not your family,

04:07.250 --> 04:10.125
and I don't feel comfortable
when you say "our family."

04:11.416 --> 04:14.416
- Chantal, is that you?

04:14.500 --> 04:16.625
- Ugh.
Yes, Daddy.

04:16.708 --> 04:19.500
I've been behind you
for 15 minutes.

04:19.583 --> 04:22.708
Oh, God.
Okay, this has got to stop.

04:22.791 --> 04:26.083
I don't like it.
You guys are freaking me out.

04:26.166 --> 04:29.083
I am not a poor person, okay?

04:29.166 --> 04:32.041
I don't want to be
a Witherbottom anymore.

04:32.125 --> 04:34.000
- Oh, but honey,
you are a Witherbottom.

04:34.083 --> 04:37.000
- This isn't Witherbottom.

04:37.083 --> 04:39.333
It's rock bottom.

04:45.750 --> 04:48.958
<i>[faint TV chatter]</i>

04:52.291 --> 04:55.250
I'm sorry.
What are you doing?

04:55.333 --> 04:59.041
- Eating, Chantal,
like a family.

04:59.125 --> 05:00.333
- Hmm.

05:00.416 --> 05:02.583
Uh, I don't think
that you are eating

05:02.666 --> 05:04.791
because I don't see food.

05:04.875 --> 05:09.750
Sticks and rings are not food.
[scoffs]

05:09.833 --> 05:12.291
- I was resistant at first,

05:12.375 --> 05:15.166
but the nuggets
have really proved themselves.

05:15.250 --> 05:17.916
They can be a little salty,
which is why it's good

05:18.000 --> 05:21.375
to take a little dip
into the sweet and the sour.

05:21.458 --> 05:22.916
It's a pleasing balance.

05:23.000 --> 05:26.083
- Catherine, your husband
is very high right now.

05:26.166 --> 05:27.875
- Can you just...
- [snorts]

05:29.541 --> 05:32.333
- [sighs]
Okay, I am not eating this.

05:32.416 --> 05:36.125
- Just think of dinner time
like we're at a carnival.

05:36.958 --> 05:38.583
- I want goose!

05:38.666 --> 05:40.625
- You've never had goose.

05:40.708 --> 05:42.833
- Yeah, okay, and you have?

05:42.916 --> 05:44.000
- Okay...

05:44.083 --> 05:45.666
- [scoffs]

05:50.958 --> 05:52.791
[quavers]

05:52.875 --> 05:56.166
It's crazy that I ate better
in prison than this.

05:56.250 --> 05:57.875
- So, Chantal,

05:57.958 --> 06:00.708
everyone is trying
to do their parts

06:00.791 --> 06:03.416
to help the family out
in their own way.

06:03.500 --> 06:06.625
Catherine is selling
bus vacations over the phone.

06:06.708 --> 06:09.916
Linda found a way to make money
off of emails.

06:10.000 --> 06:12.583
- Mm-hmm.
Every CC is 20¢.

06:12.666 --> 06:15.583
- Robert is...

06:15.666 --> 06:17.500
unable to work,

06:17.583 --> 06:19.791
and I am busy

06:19.875 --> 06:22.000
challenging the frontiers
of perception

06:22.083 --> 06:24.541
in an attempt to save us all,

06:24.625 --> 06:27.500
and so I think it may
be up to you, Chantal,

06:27.583 --> 06:29.458
to begin applying for jobs.

06:29.541 --> 06:32.166
- Oh, my friend Binda
could get you a job

06:32.250 --> 06:34.458
at a money order service
in Queens.

06:34.541 --> 06:36.791
- And I did overhear
the neighbors yelling

06:36.875 --> 06:39.500
about needing someone
to take care of their baby.

06:39.583 --> 06:41.541
You could ask about that.

06:43.666 --> 06:47.333
- [sobbing]

06:47.416 --> 06:49.291
No!

06:49.375 --> 06:50.625
- [sighs]

06:50.708 --> 06:54.083
- I want a different life!

06:54.166 --> 06:57.458
And I want all of you
to be different.

06:57.541 --> 06:59.416
I don't want to change--
I like how I am--

06:59.500 --> 07:02.208
but I want everything else
to change!

07:03.041 --> 07:06.041
Excuse me from the "table."

07:06.125 --> 07:07.791
[sobs]

07:10.791 --> 07:12.416
[sighs]

07:15.125 --> 07:16.791
[whimpers]

07:18.958 --> 07:21.916
<i>[spacey music]</i>

07:22.000 --> 07:29.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:44.208 --> 07:46.166
Why don't I feel anything?

07:46.250 --> 07:47.833
[sighs]

07:49.666 --> 07:52.291
Dare I check
the expiration dates?

07:52.375 --> 07:55.333
<i>[mellow dance music]</i>

07:55.416 --> 08:02.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:15.625 --> 08:18.333
- We've been waiting for you,
Chantal.

08:18.416 --> 08:20.291
- Take a seat.

08:20.375 --> 08:22.958
<i>[classical music]</i>

08:23.041 --> 08:30.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:31.125 --> 08:32.666
- Who are you?

08:32.750 --> 08:35.416
- [chuckles]
You tell us.

08:35.500 --> 08:38.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:38.291 --> 08:40.666
- Oh, my God.

08:40.750 --> 08:44.291
Are you the most famous
dead authors in the world?

08:44.375 --> 08:46.250
- [laughs]
all: We are.

08:46.333 --> 08:48.416
- We are.

08:48.500 --> 08:49.750
Should we go
around the table

08:49.833 --> 08:51.000
and introduce ourselves?

08:51.083 --> 08:53.625
- Let's let Chantal do it.

08:53.708 --> 08:56.291
- Oh, that's a good idea.

08:56.375 --> 08:59.291
- F. Scott Fitzgerald.
[laughs]

08:59.375 --> 09:02.791
William Shakespeare.

09:02.875 --> 09:04.833
Mr. James Baldwin.

09:04.916 --> 09:06.333
Mark Twain!
Hi.

09:06.416 --> 09:08.750
Oh, Virginia Woolf.

09:08.833 --> 09:12.083
Mm, Sylvia Plath.

09:12.166 --> 09:13.958
Maya Angelou.

09:14.041 --> 09:17.250
You're, like,
my biggest inspiration.

09:17.333 --> 09:19.416
- Same.

09:19.500 --> 09:23.166
- [laughs]

09:23.250 --> 09:25.458
And wait.

09:25.541 --> 09:27.125
Are you R. L. Stine?

09:27.208 --> 09:29.541
- That's right.

09:29.625 --> 09:31.458
I thought you were alive.

09:31.541 --> 09:34.666
- Now there's something
we need you to do for us,

09:34.750 --> 09:36.083
Chantal.

09:36.166 --> 09:37.458
- What is it?

09:37.541 --> 09:39.291
- You need to write a book.

09:39.375 --> 09:43.833
- You need to tell the world
about your mean family,

09:43.916 --> 09:46.333
about your jerk sister.

09:46.416 --> 09:48.500
She can't act like that
and expect you

09:48.583 --> 09:50.458
not to write a book about her.

09:50.541 --> 09:54.041
- But I don't know how
to write a book like that.

09:54.125 --> 09:57.500
I only know how to write poems
really well.

09:57.583 --> 09:59.916
- Oh, well, we know that.
We love your poetry.

10:00.000 --> 10:02.291
It's all we read now.

10:02.375 --> 10:06.041
- I've burned everything
that isn't your poetry,

10:06.125 --> 10:08.125
even the things I need.

10:08.208 --> 10:09.333
[laughs]

10:09.416 --> 10:11.833
- That's why we're here.
We can help you.

10:11.916 --> 10:15.125
- Let us speak through you,
Chantal.

10:15.208 --> 10:17.500
You're the vessel.

10:17.583 --> 10:18.666
- I am?

10:18.750 --> 10:22.416
- Do the world
a beautiful favor

10:22.500 --> 10:26.041
and express
what is inside of you.

10:26.125 --> 10:29.375
- Drink from this
goblet of wine,

10:29.458 --> 10:31.833
and may the passage of wisdom

10:31.916 --> 10:33.500
be complete.

10:33.583 --> 10:37.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:37.291 --> 10:40.708
[laughter]

10:40.791 --> 10:46.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:54.416 --> 10:58.166
- [sputters]

10:58.250 --> 11:01.208
<i>[driving classical music]</i>

11:01.291 --> 11:04.541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:04.625 --> 11:06.916
- Hey, uh, Chantal?

11:07.000 --> 11:08.708
Can I talk to you for a second?

11:08.791 --> 11:09.833
- [sighs]
Can it wait?

11:09.916 --> 11:11.083
I'm kind of on a roll.

11:11.166 --> 11:13.083
- No, it can't wait, okay?

11:14.916 --> 11:16.375
Look, uh,

11:16.458 --> 11:18.750
I have a lot
of unexpressed anger

11:18.833 --> 11:21.708
toward you
about how you handled

11:21.791 --> 11:23.208
my miscarriage.

11:24.666 --> 11:26.125
You didn't even
acknowledge it

11:26.208 --> 11:27.500
or ask how I was,

11:27.583 --> 11:28.916
and it's just--
it's hard for me to--

11:29.000 --> 11:30.708
- Shh!

11:30.791 --> 11:33.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:33.458 --> 11:35.416
- Wow.
Okay.

11:35.500 --> 11:37.583
[sniffling]

11:37.666 --> 11:42.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:42.500 --> 11:44.708
- Yes, yes, yes!

11:44.791 --> 11:47.541
Yes!
Yes!

11:47.625 --> 11:49.500
Yes!

11:49.583 --> 11:51.416
- Chantal, you didn't hear
what I was doing

11:51.500 --> 11:53.791
in the other room, did you?

11:53.875 --> 11:56.666
- No, Ted, I'm trying to focus.

11:56.750 --> 11:58.166
- Now I'm embarrassed.

11:59.625 --> 12:02.041
Part of me wants to tell you
what I was doing.

12:02.125 --> 12:08.708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:12.625 --> 12:14.333
- I'm done.

12:14.416 --> 12:16.458
I did it!
Ha!

12:16.541 --> 12:18.666
No, no.

12:18.750 --> 12:20.625
We did it.

12:20.708 --> 12:22.250
Thank you, friends.

12:22.333 --> 12:23.458
- What?

12:25.083 --> 12:26.875
- [quietly] Fuck you.

12:28.291 --> 12:31.166
[breathes deeply]

12:31.250 --> 12:33.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:33.750 --> 12:35.250
- Well, what can I say?
I read it.

12:35.333 --> 12:36.500
We all read it.

12:36.583 --> 12:38.083
I think everyone
in the building read it.

12:38.166 --> 12:40.833
- Oh, that's great.
[laughs]

12:40.916 --> 12:43.666
- Yeah, it's fascinating,
to say the least.

12:43.750 --> 12:45.791
Parts of it
are extremely problematic.

12:45.875 --> 12:48.583
- Mm.
- It's a very difficult read.

12:48.666 --> 12:49.833
- Yes.

12:49.916 --> 12:52.500
I--I wanted to challenge
the reader.

12:52.583 --> 12:54.208
Good books do that.

12:54.291 --> 12:55.875
- No, I mean
literally difficult.

12:55.958 --> 12:57.333
It took me eight minutes

12:57.416 --> 12:59.166
just to figure out
how to open the lock.

12:59.250 --> 13:00.250
- Right.

13:00.333 --> 13:03.083
It's supposed to look
and feel

13:03.166 --> 13:04.333
like a diary.

13:04.416 --> 13:05.666
- [chuckles]

13:05.750 --> 13:07.916
- But I feel like
if you didn't get that,

13:08.000 --> 13:10.291
then you didn't even
really understand

13:10.375 --> 13:12.208
the book that you were reading.

13:12.291 --> 13:14.291
- Yeah, well, you know,
it's unappealing.

13:14.375 --> 13:16.458
Right?
I mean, look how ugly this is.

13:16.541 --> 13:17.500
[laughs]

13:17.583 --> 13:19.125
And very costly,
I would imagine.

13:19.208 --> 13:21.541
I think you'd have to charge
the consumer at least $65

13:21.625 --> 13:23.583
just to make a profit
because of these materials.

13:23.666 --> 13:25.166
This is real leather.

13:25.250 --> 13:27.500
It's ugly leather,
but it is real, and it's heavy.

13:27.583 --> 13:29.000
I mean, whoo!

13:29.083 --> 13:30.375
You know, you can't
just carry this in your bag

13:30.458 --> 13:32.375
or throw it
in your coat pocket.

13:32.458 --> 13:34.791
And also, the title, right?
"Imperfect Ten."

13:34.875 --> 13:37.875
I don't understand.
What does that mean to you?

13:37.958 --> 13:41.708
- Well, it means
that my whole life

13:41.791 --> 13:43.666
has been a series
of realizations

13:43.750 --> 13:45.916
that even though
the common person

13:46.000 --> 13:48.708
might think
that I am a perfect ten,

13:48.791 --> 13:51.041
I am indeed flawed.

13:51.125 --> 13:52.625
I may still be a ten,

13:52.708 --> 13:54.500
but I am not perfect.

13:54.583 --> 13:56.791
- And you're just going
by Chantal?

13:56.875 --> 13:58.416
You're a one-name person?

13:58.500 --> 14:00.833
- Well, if that also
wasn't clear in the book,

14:00.916 --> 14:02.583
I hate my family,
so there's, like,

14:02.666 --> 14:05.208
no reason for me to keep
my last name anymore.

14:05.291 --> 14:06.958
- Okay, um,

14:07.041 --> 14:09.750
I don't think that you
should be a writer.

14:09.833 --> 14:12.250
In fact, I ask you
to never write again.

14:12.333 --> 14:14.000
This book is deranged,

14:14.083 --> 14:16.833
and not in a way
that I can work with it.

14:16.916 --> 14:18.708
If I were to publish this,

14:18.791 --> 14:20.625
people would freak out.

14:20.708 --> 14:23.208
It would make the world
a worse place.

14:23.291 --> 14:26.208
<i>[pensive music]</i>

14:26.291 --> 14:28.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:28.666 --> 14:32.166
- But I'm the one.

14:32.250 --> 14:34.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:34.083 --> 14:37.250
[panting]

14:49.041 --> 14:52.333
You're so stupid, Chantal!

14:55.875 --> 14:59.958
None of your dreams
are ever gonna come true.

15:00.041 --> 15:05.500
You're just
a stupid loser idiot!

15:05.583 --> 15:07.833
<i>[spacey music]</i>

15:07.916 --> 15:09.916
[cries]

15:10.000 --> 15:14.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:14.666 --> 15:17.041
- Get back here!
[yelps]

15:17.125 --> 15:18.666
[woman shouts]
- My God!

15:18.750 --> 15:20.166
- Is that a book?

15:20.250 --> 15:22.375
Charlie?
Help!

15:22.458 --> 15:24.750
My friend was hit by a book!

15:24.833 --> 15:26.750
Where did that come from?

15:26.833 --> 15:29.041
Oh, God.
Oh, God.

15:29.125 --> 15:31.166
Charlie.
Oh, fuck.

15:31.250 --> 15:33.666
Call Lorraine.

15:33.750 --> 15:35.541
Oh, God.
Oh, God.

15:35.625 --> 15:37.833
She was hit by a book!

15:37.916 --> 15:40.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:40.750 --> 15:45.750
- "Imperfect Ten" by Chantal.

15:45.833 --> 15:49.000
I wonder what that means.

15:49.083 --> 15:50.166
Hmm.

15:50.250 --> 15:54.000
<i>[driven classical music]</i>

15:54.083 --> 15:56.708
[laughs]

15:58.958 --> 16:01.541
Oh.

16:01.625 --> 16:06.916
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:07.000 --> 16:09.708
Listen up, everybody.

16:09.791 --> 16:14.291
I found a book on the street,

16:14.375 --> 16:17.708
and it's brilliant.

16:17.791 --> 16:20.208
It makes me wonder
if I should've been

16:20.291 --> 16:23.041
scouring the streets
all these years,

16:23.125 --> 16:25.541
looking down
instead of looking up.

16:25.625 --> 16:27.625
Let everyone else look up!

16:27.708 --> 16:31.041
Now, here's the kicker
about this book.

16:31.125 --> 16:35.541
It's written
by a ten-year-old little girl.

16:35.625 --> 16:38.750
- Wow.
- It's a work of art--

16:38.833 --> 16:42.250
somewhere between self-help
and a manifesto

16:42.333 --> 16:47.583
on how to live without shame
and without awareness.

16:47.666 --> 16:51.791
There's a passage
in the chapter "Picky Eater"

16:51.875 --> 16:53.458
that will break your heart.

16:53.541 --> 16:57.083
Whoever this little Chantal is,

16:57.166 --> 16:59.750
she's a genius.

16:59.833 --> 17:01.083
Yeah.

17:01.166 --> 17:04.125
<i>[spacey percussive music]</i>

17:04.208 --> 17:11.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:39.166 --> 17:40.958
- [laughs softly]

17:41.041 --> 17:43.250
Are you k...

17:43.333 --> 17:44.875
A child?

17:47.375 --> 17:49.125
Wait.

17:49.208 --> 17:51.375
Why does it say I'm a child?

17:53.375 --> 17:55.958
- I'm Wilma.
It's nice to meet you both.

17:56.041 --> 17:59.875
- I'm Helen, and this
is my daughter, Chantal.

17:59.958 --> 18:01.625
- I'm Chantal.

18:01.708 --> 18:03.625
- Well, I really hope
that's true,

18:03.708 --> 18:07.500
but there's a long line
of little girls out there,

18:07.583 --> 18:11.125
all claiming
that they wrote this book.

18:11.208 --> 18:13.166
So, Chantal,

18:13.250 --> 18:16.791
if that is in fact your name,
if you wrote this book,

18:16.875 --> 18:20.208
you would recognize
your own words, correct?

18:20.291 --> 18:21.541
Good.

18:21.625 --> 18:24.208
So I'm gonna go ahead
and quote from the book,

18:24.291 --> 18:27.625
and I want you
to finish the quote for me,

18:27.708 --> 18:30.541
and this way, I will know
if you are indeed the author.

18:30.625 --> 18:32.416
Kay?

18:32.500 --> 18:35.000
"Life is a roller coaster.

18:35.083 --> 18:36.833
"Time is the tracks,

18:36.916 --> 18:41.083
and wisdom is the..." what?

18:44.416 --> 18:45.875
- Don't look at me.

18:45.958 --> 18:48.208
You wrote it, Chantal.

18:48.291 --> 18:51.541
Wisdom is the...

18:51.625 --> 18:54.291
- Is the screams?

18:54.375 --> 18:56.625
- [sighs]
Shame on you both.

18:56.708 --> 18:58.291
- You are such
a disappointment.

18:58.375 --> 19:00.083
It's no wonder
that your father left.

19:00.166 --> 19:01.833
Excuse you!

19:04.083 --> 19:05.875
- What?
- We found her.

19:05.958 --> 19:07.875
- Are you sure?
How can you be sure?

19:07.958 --> 19:09.250
- Chantal, can you repeat

19:09.333 --> 19:11.625
what you just said to me
for Wilma?

19:11.708 --> 19:15.000
<i>- The wisdom is the park map.</i>

19:15.083 --> 19:16.375
- That's right.

19:16.458 --> 19:18.458
That's right.
The wisdom is the park map.

19:18.541 --> 19:19.875
Give me that phone.

19:19.958 --> 19:23.375
Chantal,
I am so, so happy

19:23.458 --> 19:24.958
to have found you.

19:25.041 --> 19:29.500
- Oh, my God, and I am so,
so happy to have been found!

19:29.583 --> 19:31.375
[laughs]
<i>- Oh, Chantal.</i>

19:31.458 --> 19:33.958
I don't know
if you understand

19:34.041 --> 19:35.958
what you did,

19:36.041 --> 19:39.583
but you have basically
written the Bible!

19:39.666 --> 19:40.625
- [laughs]

19:40.708 --> 19:42.375
<i>- This thing is a manifesto</i>

19:42.458 --> 19:46.750
<i>on how to be</i>
<i>a fully realized human being</i>

19:46.833 --> 19:49.083
<i>at the age of ten.</i>

19:49.166 --> 19:53.250
<i>I mean, no one has ever</i>
<i>done that before.</i>

19:53.333 --> 19:55.875
- Thank you so much.

19:55.958 --> 19:57.625
Um...

19:57.708 --> 19:59.083
The only thing is that I--

19:59.166 --> 20:02.208
<i>- I mean,</i>
<i>I sobbed hysterically.</i>

20:02.291 --> 20:05.791
I cried for the little girl
I was.

20:05.875 --> 20:10.958
I cried for the girl
I never got to be.

20:11.041 --> 20:14.083
<i>This is a masterpiece.</i>
<i>I mean it.</i>

20:14.166 --> 20:16.791
I suppose it would mean nothing
if an adult wrote it,

20:16.875 --> 20:19.458
<i>but you wrote it,</i>

20:19.541 --> 20:21.333
<i>and I need you</i>
<i>to be on my show.</i>

20:21.416 --> 20:22.750
<i>How does that sound?</i>

20:22.833 --> 20:26.291
I want the world to love you
as much as I do.

20:26.958 --> 20:28.500
- Oh, my God.

20:32.041 --> 20:33.666
Okay.

20:33.750 --> 20:35.125
Okay, okay!

20:35.208 --> 20:37.125
Yes!
Yes, I will!

20:37.208 --> 20:39.666
- Yes, yes!
She said yes.

20:39.750 --> 20:41.583
Chantal!

20:41.666 --> 20:44.750
- [giggling]
Yes!

20:44.833 --> 20:46.833
<i>[mischievous orchestral music]</i>

20:46.916 --> 20:49.291
<i>- This is Chantal.</i>
<i>Leave a beep. [laughs]</i>

20:49.375 --> 20:51.750
<i>[answering machine tone]</i>
- Shit.

20:51.833 --> 20:54.666
[sighs]

20:54.750 --> 20:56.000
- Where's Chantal?

20:56.083 --> 20:57.833
I want to meet her
before we go on the air.

20:57.916 --> 20:59.666
- I have been trying her
all day,

20:59.750 --> 21:01.375
and I'm--I'm gonna get her.

21:01.458 --> 21:02.958
<i>- This is Chantal.</i>

21:03.041 --> 21:04.708
<i>Leave a beep. [laughs]</i>
<i>[answering machine tone]</i>

21:04.791 --> 21:06.500
- Chantal, honey.
I'm hoping you're close.

21:06.583 --> 21:09.375
Please have your parents call
me back when they get this.

21:09.458 --> 21:11.166
Wilma, I know you don't
want to hear this,

21:11.250 --> 21:13.250
but I would consider
doing an audience share circle

21:13.333 --> 21:14.500
as a backup just in case
she doesn't--

21:14.583 --> 21:15.666
- No.

21:15.750 --> 21:17.208
I promised my audience Chantal,

21:17.291 --> 21:19.083
and I'm going
to give them Chantal.

21:19.166 --> 21:20.375
That's my job.

21:20.458 --> 21:22.458
Your job is to make sure
she gets here.

21:22.541 --> 21:23.916
- Show starts in five.

21:24.000 --> 21:25.250
- I'm gonna go out there,

21:25.333 --> 21:27.083
and I'm going
to introduce Chantal,

21:27.166 --> 21:29.500
and I expect for her
to come on stage

21:29.583 --> 21:31.333
the moment I call her,
got it?

21:31.416 --> 21:33.208
- [muttering indistinctly]

21:33.291 --> 21:35.541
<i>[mischievous music]</i>

21:35.625 --> 21:39.500
[phone buzzing]

21:39.583 --> 21:40.875
- Hello?

21:40.958 --> 21:42.541
- Chantal!
Are you close?

21:42.625 --> 21:46.166
- Yeah, I'm in a cab.
I'm, like, three blocks away.

21:46.250 --> 21:47.833
- Sweetie, could you please

21:47.916 --> 21:49.458
put one of your parents
on the phone?

21:49.541 --> 21:52.541
I just want to check
that you're actually close.

21:52.625 --> 21:56.000
- Oh, wait.
Look, yeah, here we are.

21:56.083 --> 21:57.541
We're here.

21:57.625 --> 22:00.041
<i>We're--we're--we're pulling up</i>
<i>to the curb.</i>

22:00.125 --> 22:02.833
We're--we're getting out.
Thank you.

22:02.916 --> 22:04.666
We're just paying the driver,
so...

22:04.750 --> 22:05.708
<i>- Oh, thank God.</i>

22:05.791 --> 22:07.041
Okay, there's unfortunately

22:07.125 --> 22:08.375
not enough time
for you to meet Wilma

22:08.458 --> 22:10.041
before the show,
but don't worry.

22:10.125 --> 22:11.500
We're gonna prep you
about everything you need to do

22:11.583 --> 22:13.375
once you get here,
so hurry, Chantal.

22:13.458 --> 22:14.791
Run.

22:14.875 --> 22:22.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:24.375 --> 22:27.166
- [sighs]
Okay.

22:27.250 --> 22:30.750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:30.833 --> 22:32.000
- All right, y'all.

22:32.083 --> 22:34.083
When that applause light
comes on,

22:34.166 --> 22:36.166
I want y'all to lose
your damn minds.

22:36.250 --> 22:37.583
You hear me?
Right.

22:37.666 --> 22:39.083
As long as that light is on,
don't stop.

22:39.166 --> 22:41.250
Keep going, keep clapping.
That's right.

22:41.333 --> 22:43.708
And you are not allowed
to stop applauding

22:43.791 --> 22:45.583
as long as that light is on.

22:45.666 --> 22:47.000
Okay?
Okay?

22:47.083 --> 22:48.833
Okay? Okay?
Yeah.

22:48.916 --> 22:50.083
All right.

22:50.166 --> 22:51.458
[laughter]
All right, here we go.

22:51.541 --> 22:53.583
Let's practice.
Show 'em that light.

22:53.666 --> 22:55.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:55.500 --> 22:58.541
<i>[cheers and applause]</i>

22:58.625 --> 23:02.750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:02.833 --> 23:04.458
That's what I'm talking--yes!
Yes!

23:04.541 --> 23:05.791
Even more.
Even more.

23:05.875 --> 23:06.958
I can feel it.
You got some more in you.

23:07.041 --> 23:08.291
I want to make it sound like

23:08.375 --> 23:09.458
the animals just broke out
of the zoo!

23:09.541 --> 23:10.416
Give it to me!

23:10.500 --> 23:11.875
Ooh, Lord have mercy.

23:11.958 --> 23:15.416
[wild cheers and applause]

23:15.500 --> 23:20.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:20.333 --> 23:21.833
- Okay.

23:21.916 --> 23:23.416
Hello.

23:23.500 --> 23:25.791
Um, I'm Chantal.

23:25.875 --> 23:28.291
- But--are you her mom?

23:28.375 --> 23:32.958
- No.
I'm...her.

23:33.041 --> 23:34.791
- But you're old.

23:34.875 --> 23:37.291
- I'm 29.
That's hardly old.

23:37.375 --> 23:38.791
- Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

23:38.875 --> 23:40.500
I can't believe this.
- We're about to go live.

23:40.583 --> 23:42.541
- [whispers] She's not a child.
She's an adult.

23:42.625 --> 23:44.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:44.541 --> 23:46.625
- Oh, Jesus.
Oh, no.

23:46.708 --> 23:49.166
Oh, no.
We have to tell her.

23:49.250 --> 23:51.000
We can't let this woman

23:51.083 --> 23:52.791
go out there
on live television.

23:52.875 --> 23:54.500
- Well, I can't tell her.
Wilma will kill me.

23:54.583 --> 23:57.250
She will actually kill me.
You tell her.

23:57.333 --> 23:59.500
- I absolutely
am not gonna tell her.

23:59.583 --> 24:02.000
I can't lose my job, Frankie.
You do it.

24:02.083 --> 24:03.333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:03.416 --> 24:05.000
- I quit.

24:05.083 --> 24:06.791
I quit.

24:06.875 --> 24:13.541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:13.625 --> 24:16.583
<i>[upbeat music playing]</i>

24:16.666 --> 24:19.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:19.583 --> 24:23.000
- And now I have the honor
of introducing

24:23.083 --> 24:25.750
a very special guest--

24:25.833 --> 24:28.583
a hero, a friend,

24:28.666 --> 24:30.541
a child.

24:30.625 --> 24:31.791
Chantal!

24:31.875 --> 24:35.083
[cheers and applause]

24:44.083 --> 24:46.125
Do we have her?

24:48.125 --> 24:50.000
Oh, maybe she's shy.

24:50.083 --> 24:51.875
You know how kids are.

24:51.958 --> 24:54.166
Even prodigies get shy.

24:54.250 --> 24:56.750
Let's make her feel welcome.

24:56.833 --> 24:58.375
Chantal!
Chantal!

24:58.458 --> 25:01.750
[all chanting]
Chantal! Chantal! Chantal!

25:16.250 --> 25:18.125
[chanting fades]

25:18.208 --> 25:21.708
[audience murmuring]

25:21.791 --> 25:23.500
- I'm sorry.
What's happening?

25:25.125 --> 25:26.916
- I'm Chantal.

25:27.000 --> 25:30.041
- I don't think so.
No.

25:30.125 --> 25:31.250
Frankie?

25:31.333 --> 25:33.625
Frankie,
who is this adult woman?

25:33.708 --> 25:35.250
- I--I can explain.

25:35.333 --> 25:37.916
- I hope you can explain
where Chantal is.

25:38.708 --> 25:41.041
- She's right here.

25:43.916 --> 25:46.958
Ten years old or not,
my book spoke to you.

25:47.041 --> 25:48.291
Right?

25:48.375 --> 25:50.041
You had an emotional
experience,

25:50.125 --> 25:53.083
and that's--that's really all
that we can ask for in life,

25:53.166 --> 25:56.625
is an emotional experience
that--that changes us.

25:57.458 --> 25:58.500
- Fuck you.

25:58.583 --> 26:00.041
[all gasp]

26:01.750 --> 26:03.375
- I'm sorry.

26:03.458 --> 26:07.791
I have not used that word
in 35 years,

26:07.875 --> 26:10.375
but I'm so full of rage
right now!

26:10.458 --> 26:13.041
You tricked me
to receive acclaim.

26:13.125 --> 26:14.500
- I didn't mean to.

26:14.583 --> 26:16.458
I truly was just trying
to find my purpose,

26:16.541 --> 26:19.625
like, you know, a sense
of belonging in the world,

26:19.708 --> 26:22.541
and isn't that
what we all want?

26:22.625 --> 26:24.291
Wilma, even you?

26:24.375 --> 26:28.625
Some sign that we're, like,
even here on this Earth

26:28.708 --> 26:30.583
for a reason?

26:30.666 --> 26:32.500
So maybe I'm not ten.

26:32.583 --> 26:34.833
Maybe I haven't been ten
for 19 years,

26:34.916 --> 26:38.708
but I know what it is
to have your heart stomped on,

26:38.791 --> 26:40.416
and I know what it is
to feel like

26:40.500 --> 26:42.166
the whole world is against you,

26:42.250 --> 26:45.083
because you know what, Wilma?

26:45.166 --> 26:47.875
I am Chantal.

26:50.541 --> 26:53.666
[applause]

27:04.416 --> 27:07.458
[cheers and applause]

27:07.541 --> 27:10.250
- Stop it.
Stop clapping.

27:10.333 --> 27:11.458
Don't clap!

27:11.541 --> 27:13.500
Everybody,
stop clapping for her.

27:13.583 --> 27:15.416
- No, let them.

27:15.500 --> 27:19.208
They want to.
They know what's good.

27:19.291 --> 27:23.416
[applause continues]

27:23.500 --> 27:25.000
- She's a fraud.

27:25.083 --> 27:27.000
Stop clapping, everybody!

27:27.083 --> 27:30.250
<i>I will not stand</i>
<i>for this kind of entitlement</i>

27:30.333 --> 27:31.958
<i>on my stage.</i>

27:32.041 --> 27:33.250
<i>This is preposterous.</i>

27:33.333 --> 27:35.708
<i>Who do you think you are?</i>

27:35.791 --> 27:38.708
<i>- Honestly...</i>

27:38.791 --> 27:40.208
<i>myself.</i>

27:40.291 --> 27:41.666
<i>[dark music]</i>

27:41.750 --> 27:46.166
<i>Honestly, myself.</i>

27:46.250 --> 27:47.750
- [gasps]

27:47.833 --> 27:50.541
<i>- Honestly, myself.</i>

27:50.625 --> 27:51.875
- Not guilty.

27:51.958 --> 27:54.583
<i>- Honestly...</i>

27:54.666 --> 27:56.208
<i>myself.</i>

27:56.291 --> 27:59.083
<i>Honestly,</i>

27:59.166 --> 28:00.125
<i>myself.</i>

28:00.208 --> 28:01.333
[woman shouts]

28:01.416 --> 28:03.916
<i>Honestly, myself.</i>

28:04.000 --> 28:07.166
<i>Honestly, myself.</i>

28:07.250 --> 28:08.541
[Taser zapping]

28:08.625 --> 28:10.125
<i>Honestly, myself.</i>

28:10.208 --> 28:12.958
- Chantal,
who are you hiding from?

28:13.041 --> 28:14.958
- Honestly,

28:15.041 --> 28:17.458
myself.

28:17.541 --> 28:19.541
- [screams]

28:19.625 --> 28:22.541
<i>[eerie music]</i>

28:22.625 --> 28:29.791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:02.416 --> 29:03.875
- [coughs]
